WEBVTT

00:00.868 --> 00:06.905
♪

00:06.907 --> 00:09.875
Best: Sometimes I have a hard
time coming up with a word

00:09.877 --> 00:12.177
That explains karl.

00:12.179 --> 00:14.580
♪

00:14.582 --> 00:16.448
"evil" just doesn't seem
strong enough.

00:16.450 --> 00:17.916
"diabolical."

00:17.918 --> 00:20.986
You know, he is just a monster.

00:20.988 --> 00:23.322
A monster.

00:23.324 --> 00:26.692
And I was married to him.

00:26.694 --> 00:29.228
I was married to him
for 18 years.

00:29.230 --> 00:34.333
♪

00:34.335 --> 00:39.438
♪

00:39.440 --> 00:43.842
I would have thoughts, thinking
"who is this man,

00:43.844 --> 00:47.312
And what lurks
behind those eyes?"

00:47.314 --> 00:56.455
♪

00:56.457 --> 00:59.224
I was very adamant

00:59.226 --> 01:02.661
And driven
to get enough evidence

01:02.663 --> 01:04.663
Or whatever I could do

01:04.665 --> 01:09.368
To get somebody to believe me.

01:09.370 --> 01:11.670
But I had to be careful.

01:11.672 --> 01:13.738
♪

01:13.740 --> 01:16.141
Every night, I would wonder,

01:16.143 --> 01:19.678
"is this the night
that I'm going to die?"

01:19.680 --> 01:22.281
[ the paper chase's "what's so
amazing about grace?" plays ]

01:22.283 --> 01:25.284
[ strings continue
playing sinister tune ]

01:25.286 --> 01:27.453
[ static crackling ]

01:27.455 --> 01:30.355
♪

01:30.357 --> 01:32.124
[ knock on door ]
[ creaking ]

01:32.126 --> 01:34.126
[ banging on door ]

01:34.128 --> 01:37.296
♪

01:37.298 --> 01:39.164
[ creaking ]

01:39.166 --> 01:42.568
♪

01:42.570 --> 01:45.204
[ water dripping ]

01:45.206 --> 01:47.873
[ banging on door ]
[ creaking ]

01:47.875 --> 01:49.608
[ sinister chord strikes ]

01:49.610 --> 01:52.611
-- Captions by vitac --
 www.Vitac.Com

01:52.613 --> 01:56.715
Captions paid for by
discovery communications

01:56.717 --> 02:01.386
Growing up, I always knew
that my aspirations in life

02:01.388 --> 02:04.623
Was just to be a mom.

02:04.625 --> 02:06.358
But the doctors had told me

02:06.360 --> 02:09.294
That I probably wouldn't be able
to conceive naturally.

02:09.296 --> 02:12.831
I had, you know,
some fertility issues.

02:12.833 --> 02:16.034
The night I met karl,
my aunt and I had decided

02:16.036 --> 02:18.003
That we were going
to go line-dancing.

02:18.005 --> 02:21.206
[ indistinct conversations ]

02:21.208 --> 02:22.341
This is a cool place.

02:22.343 --> 02:23.675
Yeah, it's really cute.

02:23.677 --> 02:26.778
-Yeah, so are the guys.
-Oh, my god. Stop.

02:26.780 --> 02:29.982
And my aunt pointed out a man

02:29.984 --> 02:32.251
That was standing at the bar.

02:32.253 --> 02:35.854
She was encouraging me
and elbowing me

02:35.856 --> 02:38.757
And saying, you know,
"he's handsome.

02:38.759 --> 02:43.595
This might be the guy for you."

02:43.597 --> 02:44.897
-Hi, ladies.
-Hi.

02:44.899 --> 02:47.366
-How are you guys doing tonight?
-Oh, we're having fun.

02:47.368 --> 02:50.602
Best:
And he asked, very politely,

02:50.604 --> 02:52.971
"I'd like to buy you a drink."

02:52.973 --> 02:56.475
And we just started
talking from there.

02:56.477 --> 03:00.612
What intrigued me a lot
about him was the fact

03:00.614 --> 03:04.616
That he was a single dad
with three children.

03:04.618 --> 03:07.786
He had two girls and a boy,

03:07.788 --> 03:10.389
So I looked at it as, you know,

03:10.391 --> 03:14.993
"this might be my opportunity
to have my dream come true."

03:14.995 --> 03:24.703
♪

03:24.705 --> 03:34.446
♪

03:34.448 --> 03:37.816
That night is when
he told the story

03:37.818 --> 03:41.153
About his first wife

03:41.155 --> 03:44.423
Dying in a fire
in california one year ago.

03:44.425 --> 03:48.894
I was doing some repairs,
um, and...

03:48.896 --> 03:51.997
I just heard screaming
from the house.

03:51.999 --> 03:53.532
Oh, my god.

03:53.534 --> 03:58.270
Karl had said that he had
been out in the garage working,

03:58.272 --> 04:01.940
And he had heard her screaming,

04:01.942 --> 04:03.775
"karl, get the children."

04:03.777 --> 04:06.111
And he looked and realized

04:06.113 --> 04:09.581
That the house was on fire.

04:09.583 --> 04:12.050
He said he was able
to get the children out,

04:12.052 --> 04:15.787
But he was not able
to get near the bathroom,

04:15.789 --> 04:19.124
Where christina had died.

04:19.126 --> 04:22.194
I asked him, "why couldn't
she get out of the bathroom?"

04:22.196 --> 04:28.066
And karl had said that
the only window in the bathroom

04:28.068 --> 04:32.904
Had been boarded up because
a couple months before that,

04:32.906 --> 04:34.206
The window had broken.

04:34.208 --> 04:35.707
He tried to save her,

04:35.709 --> 04:38.343
But she wasn't able to escape.

04:38.345 --> 04:40.479
♪

04:40.481 --> 04:43.181
He was very distraught over it.

04:43.183 --> 04:45.617
-[ crying ]
-I'm so sorry, karl.

04:45.619 --> 04:47.819
I didn't mean
to bring this up.

04:47.821 --> 04:53.058
♪

04:53.060 --> 04:55.661
Is --
is this your wife?

04:55.663 --> 04:57.429
Can I see?

04:57.431 --> 04:59.464
♪

04:59.466 --> 05:03.468
This picture is christina.

05:03.470 --> 05:05.837
One of the first reactions I got

05:05.839 --> 05:09.174
From karl's parents

05:09.176 --> 05:12.377
When I first met them
is, you know, "oh, my gosh.

05:12.379 --> 05:15.814
You look just like christina."

05:15.816 --> 05:17.182
You know, from
what I understand,

05:17.184 --> 05:19.584
She was this great person
and had a good heart

05:19.586 --> 05:23.689
And only wanted what was best
for her children.

05:23.691 --> 05:25.924
I truly felt sorry for him.

05:25.926 --> 05:28.527
This poor man is struggling,

05:28.529 --> 05:31.163
Trying to be a single dad.

05:31.165 --> 05:34.599
The children were 6, 7, and 8 --

05:34.601 --> 05:38.704
Two girls and a boy,
levi being the middle child.

05:38.706 --> 05:41.206
Katie and levi and erin --

05:41.208 --> 05:43.642
Three children
that needed a mom,

05:43.644 --> 05:46.044
And I wanted to be a mom.

05:46.046 --> 05:49.348
Karl.

05:49.350 --> 05:55.220
And nine months after we met,
we got married.

05:55.222 --> 05:57.889
On mine and karl's wedding day,

05:57.891 --> 06:02.527
We didn't want to make
a big affair of everything.

06:02.529 --> 06:05.063
Him and I and the three kids

06:05.065 --> 06:07.866
Went in front of the justice
of the peace.

06:07.868 --> 06:10.769
This was the beginning
of my fairy tale

06:10.771 --> 06:13.705
I thought was
going to come true.

06:13.707 --> 06:17.843
And I was very happy

06:17.845 --> 06:19.811
At this point.

06:19.813 --> 06:28.487
♪

06:28.489 --> 06:30.756
Shortly after we were married,

06:30.758 --> 06:33.725
I would occasionally catch karl

06:33.727 --> 06:38.463
In telling lies.

06:38.465 --> 06:40.599
Karl?

06:40.601 --> 06:45.704
And I started noticing
he would lie about money.

06:45.706 --> 06:48.006
Hey.
We, uh --

06:48.008 --> 06:50.475
We got this
in the mail today.

06:50.477 --> 06:52.511
Yeah?
What does it say?

06:52.513 --> 06:54.813
It says we owe money.

06:54.815 --> 06:56.515
A year after we were married,

06:56.517 --> 06:59.284
I had gotten a note
from the bank

06:59.286 --> 07:03.121
That said this $2,000
loan had come due.

07:03.123 --> 07:05.757
And I asked karl about it.
I said, "what is this?

07:05.759 --> 07:10.529
Why do we owe $2,000
to the bank?"

07:10.531 --> 07:13.064
Here.

07:13.066 --> 07:14.900
And he had said it was a loan

07:14.902 --> 07:18.170
That he had taken out
before he met me.

07:18.172 --> 07:19.538
Yeah, no.
This is an old one.

07:19.540 --> 07:23.341
Can't be old.
The date's current.

07:23.343 --> 07:25.076
That did not make sense to me.

07:25.078 --> 07:26.611
Cindy, don't worry about it,
all right?

07:26.613 --> 07:29.714
I'll take care of it.

07:29.716 --> 07:30.949
All right.

07:30.951 --> 07:32.684
So, I went down to the bank

07:32.686 --> 07:35.086
And I asked them
to please tell me

07:35.088 --> 07:39.024
The date of when this loan
was first taken out.

07:39.026 --> 07:43.094
And it had been exactly a year.

07:43.096 --> 07:45.063
So I knew he lied to me.

07:45.065 --> 07:50.068
♪

07:50.070 --> 07:53.939
And I confronted him.

07:53.941 --> 07:56.875
Found out about the loan.

07:56.877 --> 07:58.710
I, uh --

07:58.712 --> 08:02.414
I looked into it,
and I saw the paperwork.

08:02.416 --> 08:03.949
So what?

08:03.951 --> 08:07.786
"this was not something that
you took out before you met me,

08:07.788 --> 08:11.523
And you lied to me,
and I want you to explain that."

08:11.525 --> 08:14.125
You're saying I'm lying?

08:14.127 --> 08:15.627
If that's what
the paperwork says.

08:15.629 --> 08:18.330
Then the paperwork
is wrong.

08:18.332 --> 08:19.798
When karl was caught in a lie,

08:19.800 --> 08:23.835
He would defend
himself vehemently.

08:23.837 --> 08:27.405
But I would not
let him win on that,

08:27.407 --> 08:32.377
And I just kept telling him,
"I know you're lying."

08:32.379 --> 08:35.747
Karl, it has
your signature on it.

08:35.749 --> 08:37.215
Why -- why can't you
be honest with me?

08:37.217 --> 08:39.050
No, no, no.
Don't give me this, okay?

08:39.052 --> 08:40.785
What do you
want me to do?

08:40.787 --> 08:43.421
♪

08:43.423 --> 08:47.292
And then he would finally admit,
"all right, okay, I did this,

08:47.294 --> 08:49.628
But I didn't think
you'd approve of it."

08:49.630 --> 08:52.964
♪

08:52.966 --> 08:54.966
Don't you
understand that?

08:54.968 --> 08:59.004
♪

08:59.006 --> 09:00.772
And he would say,
"I'm very sorry.

09:00.774 --> 09:04.309
You know, I want you
to trust me again."

09:04.311 --> 09:06.411
I'm sorry, okay?

09:06.413 --> 09:10.015
"and I won't do it again."

09:10.017 --> 09:13.818
And he wouldn't,
until the next time.

09:13.820 --> 09:16.054
There was always a next time.

09:16.056 --> 09:25.864
♪

09:25.866 --> 09:28.066
We had horses,
and I did horseback riding,

09:28.068 --> 09:30.535
Which I loved.
It was a passion of mine.

09:30.537 --> 09:33.171
Cindy.
Cindy, look.

09:33.173 --> 09:34.706
-What?
-Look -- look at this.

09:34.708 --> 09:38.510
And he came upon this horse
named ginger.

09:38.512 --> 09:40.512
Karl was very excited
about her.

09:40.514 --> 09:41.546
Look at her.

09:41.548 --> 09:43.014
-She's beautiful.
-She is.

09:43.016 --> 09:46.818
He felt that he could use her
for breeding purposes

09:46.820 --> 09:50.822
To produce prize-winning
belgian horses.

09:50.824 --> 09:53.124
So, karl thought that ginger

09:53.126 --> 09:55.226
Was going to bring in
a lot of money.

09:55.228 --> 09:57.729
Do you really think we should
spend the money on this? I --

09:57.731 --> 10:01.099
C-cindy, cindy, if we spend
the money on this,

10:01.101 --> 10:04.536
This could make us
a whole bunch later on.

10:04.538 --> 10:06.605
Karl, if you say so.

10:06.607 --> 10:13.478
♪

10:13.480 --> 10:15.213
I love this picture.

10:15.215 --> 10:17.649
That's ginger.

10:17.651 --> 10:19.250
And we had other horses,

10:19.252 --> 10:23.154
But ginger just was special.

10:23.156 --> 10:25.890
Karl just told me
that he was going to add her

10:25.892 --> 10:28.860
To the farm insurance policy,

10:28.862 --> 10:31.363
And just in case things
don't work out,

10:31.365 --> 10:34.199
Try to get back the money
that we have into her.

10:34.201 --> 10:36.267
I said, "okay.
Well, that kind of make sense."

10:36.269 --> 10:40.472
But after many attempts
of trying to breed her,

10:40.474 --> 10:42.741
He discovered
she couldn't get pregnant.

10:42.743 --> 10:48.580
♪

10:48.582 --> 10:50.382
One night, I remember

10:50.384 --> 10:53.852
Karl waking up
and going downstairs.

10:53.854 --> 10:57.155
And a few minutes later,
he came back to bed.

10:57.157 --> 11:00.892
And I asked him, you know,
"where did you go?

11:00.894 --> 11:02.494
What were you doing?"

11:02.496 --> 11:04.796
And he said, "oh,
I went to the bathroom."

11:04.798 --> 11:06.665
Well, that didn't
make sense to me,

11:06.667 --> 11:10.135
Because we had
an upstairs bathroom.

11:10.137 --> 11:13.705
But a lot of times, he would
raid the refrigerator

11:13.707 --> 11:15.073
And lie about it,

11:15.075 --> 11:19.110
So I just assumed that
he went down to the refrigerator

11:19.112 --> 11:23.248
And was just grabbing some food.

11:23.250 --> 11:25.083
Karl:
Cindy! Cindy!

11:25.085 --> 11:26.851
A few minutes later,

11:26.853 --> 11:31.056
I remember karl sitting upright
and him saying to me...

11:31.058 --> 11:32.624
-The barn's on fire!
-What? Oh, my god!

11:32.626 --> 11:34.259
Cindy:
Karl, what's happening?!

11:34.261 --> 11:36.494
..."oh, my gosh.
The barn's on fire."

11:46.039 --> 11:51.309
♪

11:51.311 --> 11:52.577
Cindy! Cindy!

11:52.579 --> 11:54.012
-What? What?
-The barn's on fire!

11:54.014 --> 11:56.347
-The barn's on fire!
-What? Oh, my god! Karl?!

11:56.349 --> 11:59.217
Best: I remember karl
sitting upright out of bed,

11:59.219 --> 12:01.486
You know, screaming,
"call 911.

12:01.488 --> 12:03.354
The barn's on fire."

12:03.356 --> 12:05.023
Can you send someone quick?

12:05.025 --> 12:07.158
Our -- our barn is on fire!

12:07.160 --> 12:09.694
It was an old barn.
It had a lot of old hay,

12:09.696 --> 12:13.431
So it kind of engulfed quickly.

12:13.433 --> 12:15.600
And it didn't take long
to realize

12:15.602 --> 12:17.869
That any horse
that might have been in there

12:17.871 --> 12:20.972
Would not survive with the fire.

12:20.974 --> 12:26.044
♪

12:26.046 --> 12:29.681
The next day,
fire investigators come out.

12:29.683 --> 12:30.982
Okay.

12:30.984 --> 12:33.651
The building --
structurally still sound.

12:33.653 --> 12:35.920
You've got a lot of repairs
you've got to do,

12:35.922 --> 12:38.056
And it seems to me...

12:38.058 --> 12:41.459
This is your source.

12:41.461 --> 12:42.894
You know, they suspected that

12:42.896 --> 12:46.097
Because there was
this old radio,

12:46.099 --> 12:49.300
Maybe the faulty wiring

12:49.302 --> 12:52.537
Sparked the hay,
and that's what caused it.

12:52.539 --> 12:56.508
So it was ruled,
you know, accidental.

12:56.510 --> 12:57.709
I'm very sorry to tell you

12:57.711 --> 13:00.411
That the animals
just did not make it.

13:00.413 --> 13:03.481
♪

13:03.483 --> 13:05.483
I really didn't
suspect anything,

13:05.485 --> 13:07.652
But I did have a question
for karl,

13:07.654 --> 13:11.389
Is, "how did you know
that the barn was on fire?"

13:11.391 --> 13:14.225
'cause you couldn't see
the barn from our window.

13:14.227 --> 13:17.796
You had to kind of
look backwards at it.

13:17.798 --> 13:20.165
Karl?

13:20.167 --> 13:21.666
Yeah.

13:21.668 --> 13:23.668
How did you know
there was a fire?

13:23.670 --> 13:26.771
I woke up,
and I heard it, cindy.

13:26.773 --> 13:31.442
And his answer to me was that
he could hear the crackling,

13:31.444 --> 13:33.578
And that's what alerted him.

13:33.580 --> 13:36.314
And I remember thinking,
"well, I didn't hear it."

13:36.316 --> 13:39.017
♪

13:39.019 --> 13:41.085
I would say within a month,

13:41.087 --> 13:45.056
We probably got
the insurance check.

13:45.058 --> 13:50.395
My recollection
is that it was for $115,000,

13:50.397 --> 13:52.831
Although karl disputes that.

13:52.833 --> 13:58.436
♪

13:58.438 --> 14:04.075
♪

14:04.077 --> 14:08.746
The first time that I ever
was scared physically,

14:08.748 --> 14:11.149
We had had an argument.

14:11.151 --> 14:14.118
It's just annoying. I mean,
every time I check the account,

14:14.120 --> 14:15.854
It's overdrawn, karl.

14:15.856 --> 14:17.589
Well, what do you want me
to say, cindy?

14:17.591 --> 14:20.191
You know, it costs a lot
of money to run a farm.

14:20.193 --> 14:21.993
When checks would come in
for the business,

14:21.995 --> 14:23.828
He would take them and cash them
and spend them,

14:23.830 --> 14:27.165
And it was a fight,
a constant fight

14:27.167 --> 14:28.833
That we had kept having.

14:28.835 --> 14:31.269
Karl, I'm sick
of having this argument.

14:31.271 --> 14:34.672
And I went to reach
for the door handle to leave.

14:34.674 --> 14:39.310
♪

14:39.312 --> 14:42.814
And he blocked the door,
and said, "you're not leaving."

14:42.816 --> 14:44.549
Sick of it?

14:44.551 --> 14:47.252
[ scoffs ]

14:47.254 --> 14:49.087
I'm sick of it, too.

14:49.089 --> 14:51.189
♪

14:51.191 --> 14:54.192
He kind of wrapped me
in a bear hug

14:54.194 --> 14:56.561
And wouldn't let me move.

14:56.563 --> 14:59.197
Karl, no, please!

14:59.199 --> 15:03.067
And the look in his eyes,
it scared me.

15:03.069 --> 15:04.669
I think he enjoyed it,

15:04.671 --> 15:08.640
That he had the upper hand
and he had control.

15:08.642 --> 15:11.109
You're hurting me!
Karl!

15:11.111 --> 15:14.545
I knew that I was not going
to be able to get free from him.

15:14.547 --> 15:17.115
I had to defuse the situation.

15:17.117 --> 15:20.618
I just had to keep
talking to him.

15:20.620 --> 15:24.422
Karl, you're scaring me.
Stop.

15:24.424 --> 15:27.125
And he did eventually.
He released me.

15:27.127 --> 15:31.696
♪

15:31.698 --> 15:36.134
And it was when I was free
that I said to him,

15:36.136 --> 15:37.335
"I just want you to know

15:37.337 --> 15:41.039
That if you ever
do that to me again,

15:41.041 --> 15:42.340
You and I are done."

15:42.342 --> 15:45.243
Okay, cindy, I'm sorry.
It wasn't --

15:45.245 --> 15:46.878
Okay.

15:46.880 --> 15:49.113
All right.

15:49.115 --> 15:52.350
But I didn't really think
at that time

15:52.352 --> 15:54.886
That I was going to leave him.

15:54.888 --> 15:58.222
Here I was, a new mom
to these children,

15:58.224 --> 16:00.325
And they had already
lost a mom,

16:00.327 --> 16:02.860
And I didn't feel like
I could do that to them.

16:02.862 --> 16:05.530
I mean, he never laid a hand
on me again after that.

16:05.532 --> 16:07.532
So I forgave him.

16:07.534 --> 16:16.641
♪

16:16.643 --> 16:20.144
We were going through in vitro
fertilization treatments

16:20.146 --> 16:22.747
To try to have
a child of my own.

16:22.749 --> 16:24.782
And after alex was born,

16:24.784 --> 16:29.620
Karl really took an active role
in being a father.

16:29.622 --> 16:32.991
That's alex on karl's shoulders.

16:32.993 --> 16:35.426
Obviously, he's pretty happy

16:35.428 --> 16:38.029
And not worried about anything.

16:38.031 --> 16:41.499
You can tell on alex's face
that he loves his dad.

16:41.501 --> 16:44.202
And this period in our lives

16:44.204 --> 16:47.338
Was one of the happiest.

16:47.340 --> 16:52.110
Yes, karl and I
had had issues in the past,

16:52.112 --> 16:55.279
But everything was
going to be okay after this,

16:55.281 --> 16:57.815
And I truly believed that.

16:57.817 --> 17:04.355
♪

17:04.357 --> 17:07.558
The brunt of his anger
was taken out on the sons.

17:07.560 --> 17:10.194
After alex was old enough
to start doing chores

17:10.196 --> 17:13.331
Is when he got angered the most.

17:13.333 --> 17:15.566
Karl:
Alex, turn it off! Cut it off!

17:15.568 --> 17:17.435
[ engine stops ]

17:17.437 --> 17:20.038
One time, I looked out
the window

17:20.040 --> 17:22.774
And saw alex on the lawnmower,

17:22.776 --> 17:26.477
And I could tell karl was
yelling at him and berating him.

17:26.479 --> 17:29.914
And alex was just sitting there
with his head down.

17:29.916 --> 17:32.450
And I thought,
"what is going on?"

17:32.452 --> 17:33.851
What did I tell you?

17:33.853 --> 17:36.554
-Go easy around the --
-what did I tell you?!

17:36.556 --> 17:38.156
Karl's very angry.

17:38.158 --> 17:40.858
And I walked out, and I said,
"what's going on?"

17:40.860 --> 17:42.193
I wasn't acting stupid.

17:42.195 --> 17:43.628
Don't you ever
talk back to me!

17:43.630 --> 17:45.496
Karl!

17:45.498 --> 17:48.699
♪

17:48.701 --> 17:51.769
And karl's demeanor
completely changed

17:51.771 --> 17:53.938
And said, "oh, nothing.
We're fine."

17:53.940 --> 17:57.141
It's all right, honey.
We're, uh --

17:57.143 --> 17:58.609
He's doing good.

17:58.611 --> 18:01.579
But I knew
that wasn't the truth.

18:01.581 --> 18:03.381
Just the look on his face --

18:03.383 --> 18:06.350
You could see the anger
in his eyes,

18:06.352 --> 18:08.953
And his fists were clenched.

18:08.955 --> 18:12.457
That's when I started thinking,
"who is this man,

18:12.459 --> 18:15.293
And what lurks
behind those eyes?"

18:15.295 --> 18:23.367
♪

18:23.369 --> 18:31.442
♪

18:31.444 --> 18:35.613
I was in disbelief
that this was happening to me.

18:37.550 --> 18:38.983
What do I do?

18:45.358 --> 18:52.096
♪

18:52.098 --> 18:56.033
Now, this is the one
that's scary.

18:56.035 --> 19:01.839
This is the one that shows
who karl karlsen is.

19:01.841 --> 19:04.742
♪

19:04.744 --> 19:08.713
Look how deranged he looks,
how crazy he looks.

19:08.715 --> 19:11.149
Look at his eyes. You can see --

19:11.151 --> 19:13.818
You can see it in his eyes.

19:13.820 --> 19:16.687
Empty eyes.

19:16.689 --> 19:19.924
Evil eyes.

19:19.926 --> 19:21.926
This is the real karl karlsen.

19:21.928 --> 19:23.861
This is who he is.

19:23.863 --> 19:32.970
♪

19:32.972 --> 19:36.240
Him and karl would just
butt heads at times.

19:36.242 --> 19:40.511
You know, levi was defiant
a lot of times, purposefully.

19:40.513 --> 19:42.013
You live in my house,
you follow my rules!

19:42.015 --> 19:43.881
I'm not listening to you
anymore, okay?

19:43.883 --> 19:45.483
You think you're so smart?

19:45.485 --> 19:47.118
I know your little secret!

19:47.120 --> 19:48.786
Oh, yeah, tough guy?
What's that?

19:48.788 --> 19:51.355
Best: When he was 17,
I remember a time

19:51.357 --> 19:54.592
When levi had accused karl

19:54.594 --> 19:56.494
Of killing his mother...

19:56.496 --> 19:58.129
-You killed mom!
-What did you just say to me?

19:58.131 --> 19:59.397
I know
you started the fire!

19:59.399 --> 20:04.135
...Actually accused him
of setting the fire.

20:04.137 --> 20:05.937
-Get off me!
-Don't you talk to me like that!

20:05.939 --> 20:08.372
Karl absolutely lost his temper

20:08.374 --> 20:11.142
And did not hold back.

20:11.144 --> 20:13.377
[ indistinct shouting ]

20:13.379 --> 20:16.814
Karl: You don't talk
to your father that way!

20:16.816 --> 20:19.550
Best: Erin and I,
it took all that we could do

20:19.552 --> 20:22.687
To get karl pulled off of levi.

20:22.689 --> 20:26.224
And levi got free of him

20:26.226 --> 20:28.659
And went out and got in
his pickup truck

20:28.661 --> 20:31.462
And was trying
to get away from karl.

20:31.464 --> 20:33.965
-Come on! Come on!
-Dad, stop! Please, stop!

20:33.967 --> 20:36.234
[ indistinct shouting ]

20:36.236 --> 20:39.070
And I remember yelling to karl,

20:39.072 --> 20:42.373
You know, "just let him go.
Just let him go."

20:42.375 --> 20:45.209
[ grunting, gasping ]

20:45.211 --> 20:47.945
And I viewed it as just

20:47.947 --> 20:51.148
Levi going through
this rebellious period.

20:51.150 --> 20:58.556
♪

20:58.558 --> 21:06.063
♪

21:06.065 --> 21:08.699
Levi started turning the corner

21:08.701 --> 21:12.336
And realizing that, "I have
to be this mature adult."

21:12.338 --> 21:16.140
Karl had a good job
at a glass company,

21:16.142 --> 21:19.076
And levi asked karl

21:19.078 --> 21:23.281
If he could maybe try
to get him a job there.

21:23.283 --> 21:25.316
So karl got him hired there.

21:25.318 --> 21:27.318
And him and karl
really seemed like

21:27.320 --> 21:30.288
They were getting along finally.

21:30.290 --> 21:36.360
♪

21:36.362 --> 21:40.264
We had to leave for
my aunt's funeral around noon,

21:40.266 --> 21:43.301
And karl had come in and said

21:43.303 --> 21:46.604
That levi was going to be
coming out to the farm that day

21:46.606 --> 21:50.041
Because he had some work
to do on his pickup truck

21:50.043 --> 21:53.344
And going to use our tools
and use the garage.

21:53.346 --> 21:56.681
Yeah, levi said he'd be here
a couple hours at least.

21:56.683 --> 21:59.984
And, you know, it got to be
noon, time for us to leave,

21:59.986 --> 22:03.854
And karl, sort of, like,
as an afterthought,

22:03.856 --> 22:05.523
Said, "wait for me in the car.

22:05.525 --> 22:08.225
I'm going to run out
and tell levi that we're leaving

22:08.227 --> 22:10.361
And make sure he has
everything that he needs."

22:10.363 --> 22:13.164
And I said, "okay."

22:13.166 --> 22:16.534
I would say that I was
waiting in the car

22:16.536 --> 22:21.072
No more than three minutes.

22:21.074 --> 22:23.507
Karl came and got
in the driver's seat,

22:23.509 --> 22:25.710
And we drove away.

22:25.712 --> 22:34.885
♪

22:34.887 --> 22:37.822
I noticed that levi's
pickup truck

22:37.824 --> 22:41.826
Was still in the same spot
as when we left.

22:41.828 --> 22:43.661
I'm gonna go tell levi
that we're back, okay?

22:43.663 --> 22:45.196
-Okay.
-All right.

22:45.198 --> 22:47.465
♪

22:47.467 --> 22:51.535
And it wasn't, you know,
30 seconds, 45 seconds

22:51.537 --> 22:55.873
That karl came up and started
banging on the window

22:55.875 --> 22:59.577
And telling me to call 911.

22:59.579 --> 23:02.113
[ distorted ] levi's been in an
accident! The truck fell on him!

23:02.115 --> 23:03.814
Call 911!

23:03.816 --> 23:12.857
♪

23:12.859 --> 23:21.899
♪

23:21.901 --> 23:30.975
♪

23:30.977 --> 23:40.017
♪

23:40.019 --> 23:49.093
♪

23:51.164 --> 23:53.164
One of the worst days
of my life.

23:53.166 --> 23:56.100
Horrible. Just horrible.

23:59.939 --> 24:03.174
♪

24:03.176 --> 24:07.044
[ sobbing loudly ]

24:07.046 --> 24:10.648
Karl seemed very distraught,

24:10.650 --> 24:13.317
Throwing himself
up against the wall.

24:15.955 --> 24:18.322
For a fleeting moment,

24:18.324 --> 24:21.392
I was thinking to myself

24:21.394 --> 24:24.495
It seemed overly distraught.

24:24.497 --> 24:26.764
[ sobbing, stammering
indistinctly ]

24:26.766 --> 24:30.034
♪

24:30.036 --> 24:33.204
It just didn't seem true to me.

24:33.206 --> 24:34.839
But then I was mad at myself
and said,

24:34.841 --> 24:38.275
"this is his biological son.
How would you act, you know,

24:38.277 --> 24:41.445
If you just found
your son dead?"

24:41.447 --> 24:49.720
♪

24:49.722 --> 24:57.962
♪

24:57.964 --> 25:03.334
I was 100% certain
that he had murdered levi.

25:03.336 --> 25:07.838
And I was afraid
that if karl found out

25:07.840 --> 25:11.342
That I even had any suspicions
about anything

25:11.344 --> 25:13.043
That he would kill me.

25:23.723 --> 25:31.428
♪

25:31.430 --> 25:33.797
Best: It was probably
a week after the funeral

25:33.799 --> 25:35.533
That karl told me

25:35.535 --> 25:39.703
That levi had actually had
a life insurance policy.

25:39.705 --> 25:41.939
And, you know, I said, "he did?"

25:41.941 --> 25:44.408
-For levi?
-Yeah. Apparently,

25:44.410 --> 25:46.844
-He had it all set up.
-Really?

25:46.846 --> 25:48.712
And then he said,
"well, I didn't know this,

25:48.714 --> 25:52.283
But he made me beneficiary
to the accounts,

25:52.285 --> 25:55.419
Because levi and his ex-wife,

25:55.421 --> 25:59.723
They kind of went through
a nasty divorce."

25:59.725 --> 26:02.960
He didn't want to make
his ex-wife beneficiary,

26:02.962 --> 26:07.331
So your next person in line
would be a parent.

26:07.333 --> 26:09.033
And that made sense to me.

26:09.035 --> 26:11.969
Seems prudent.

26:11.971 --> 26:13.404
What he first told me was

26:13.406 --> 26:17.041
The insurance was for $300,000.

26:17.043 --> 26:19.143
But then he said,
"well, I found out

26:19.145 --> 26:22.479
That there was actually
an accidental rider on it,

26:22.481 --> 26:25.749
So it's actually
worth $700,000."

26:25.751 --> 26:28.118
And I was like, "whoa,
that's a lot of money."

26:28.120 --> 26:29.954
It's, uh, worth
quite a lot.

26:29.956 --> 26:31.221
We should probably
get some advice

26:31.223 --> 26:34.592
About how to invest it
in something.

26:34.594 --> 26:36.660
I guess so.

26:36.662 --> 26:39.196
So, um,
I'll look into it.

26:39.198 --> 26:45.302
♪

26:45.304 --> 26:51.408
♪

26:51.410 --> 26:53.043
I would start
having these thoughts

26:53.045 --> 26:57.581
That maybe karl had something
to do with this.

26:57.583 --> 27:00.951
It just seemed like
too many coincidences

27:00.953 --> 27:02.820
Happened with karl

27:02.822 --> 27:06.090
For his own benefit.

27:06.092 --> 27:08.559
His first wife,

27:08.561 --> 27:10.828
The barn fire,

27:10.830 --> 27:12.296
Then all of this with levi

27:12.298 --> 27:16.233
And, you know, the insurance.

27:16.235 --> 27:19.269
But I would say, "cindy,
what are you thinking?

27:19.271 --> 27:21.038
This is your husband.

27:21.040 --> 27:23.073
Nobody does this."

27:23.075 --> 27:26.043
♪

27:26.045 --> 27:29.747
But then the thoughts would
start coming more and more.

27:29.749 --> 27:32.049
And as time went on,

27:32.051 --> 27:35.419
I kept having
these panic attacks.

27:35.421 --> 27:39.223
And they were coming
closer and closer together,

27:39.225 --> 27:42.159
And I honestly thought

27:42.161 --> 27:45.062
Maybe I was going crazy.

27:45.064 --> 27:48.365
Am I just paranoid?

27:48.367 --> 27:52.569
Whose husband would carry out
these horrible things

27:52.571 --> 27:53.904
That I'm thinking?

27:53.906 --> 27:55.239
Nobody does, you know?

27:55.241 --> 27:58.042
You don't kill
your own children.

27:58.044 --> 28:03.547
♪

28:03.549 --> 28:08.986
♪

28:08.988 --> 28:11.455
I had gone away with a friend,

28:11.457 --> 28:16.927
And it was probably
at like 4:00 in the morning.

28:16.929 --> 28:20.931
And I realized, "I've left
my son home with him.

28:20.933 --> 28:23.200
Is my son safe?"

28:23.202 --> 28:25.836
♪

28:25.838 --> 28:30.474
And I had the grand mal
of panic attacks,

28:30.476 --> 28:34.178
The worst one
that I've ever had.

28:34.180 --> 28:36.814
Nobody's going to be there
to protect him.

28:36.816 --> 28:41.251
And that was my worst,
horrifying feeling,

28:41.253 --> 28:44.421
That...

28:44.423 --> 28:48.759
[voice breaking]
I can't protect my children.

28:48.761 --> 28:51.895
A mother's job is to protect
their children, you know?

28:51.897 --> 28:54.198
When you got to protect them
from their own father,

28:54.200 --> 28:56.166
It's a horrifying feeling.

28:56.168 --> 28:59.002
[ gasping ]

28:59.004 --> 29:02.172
I got no sleep that night,

29:02.174 --> 29:06.643
And so I googled
"private investigators near me,"

29:06.645 --> 29:09.379
And one of the first ones
that come up,

29:09.381 --> 29:12.516
I met with him and asked him
if he could look into it.

29:12.518 --> 29:20.924
♪

29:20.926 --> 29:22.526
Did you find anything?

29:22.528 --> 29:24.328
Well, I got some
interesting news.

29:24.330 --> 29:26.897
My number-one concern
at this point

29:26.899 --> 29:29.700
Was, "is there a policy
out on alex?"

29:29.702 --> 29:32.202
That was one of the first things
that I had asked.

29:32.204 --> 29:34.905
First, it appears that your son
is in the clear.

29:34.907 --> 29:37.074
I wasn't able to identify
any policies on him.

29:37.076 --> 29:39.676
[ sighs ] thank god.
He told me at that time

29:39.678 --> 29:42.346
That, "no, there was
no policy on alex."

29:42.348 --> 29:45.549
So, I felt a little bit better.

29:45.551 --> 29:46.583
But...

29:46.585 --> 29:48.218
But then he said to me

29:48.220 --> 29:53.290
My granddaughters each
had $300,000 on them...

29:53.292 --> 29:56.360
No. No.

29:56.362 --> 29:58.562
...And that I was worth

29:58.564 --> 30:02.299
$1.2 million dead to karl.

30:02.301 --> 30:07.070
So, my life was probably
at risk.

30:07.072 --> 30:10.107
It's hard to explain the feeling
I was actually feeling

30:10.109 --> 30:14.545
When I found out that I was
worth so much to him dead.

30:14.547 --> 30:16.980
Panic and just frenzy.

30:16.982 --> 30:20.584
Listen, I really think
you should be careful.

30:20.586 --> 30:22.886
♪

30:22.888 --> 30:24.321
Now what do I do?

30:24.323 --> 30:32.162
♪

30:32.164 --> 30:36.700
I had considered going
to law enforcement and saying,

30:36.702 --> 30:40.370
"I think this. I think this.
I think this."

30:40.372 --> 30:43.974
But you have to realize
that in seneca county,

30:43.976 --> 30:47.978
The karlsens are well-known.

30:47.980 --> 30:52.883
And I was afraid that
if I went to law enforcement

30:52.885 --> 30:56.486
With any suspicions,
and they didn't believe me,

30:56.488 --> 30:59.156
That somebody would tip karl off

30:59.158 --> 31:02.392
To what I was doing.

31:02.394 --> 31:05.429
And so I decided to carry on

31:05.431 --> 31:07.764
As we normally would.

31:07.766 --> 31:10.367
♪

31:10.369 --> 31:12.669
Karl, through
our whole marriage,

31:12.671 --> 31:14.771
Sex was very important to him.

31:14.773 --> 31:20.277
And even when I knew
that he was a murderer,

31:20.279 --> 31:24.314
I still had to give in
to his desires,

31:24.316 --> 31:26.817
Because if I didn't,

31:26.819 --> 31:30.687
It was going to raise red flags.

31:30.689 --> 31:35.959
I have to act like
nothing is out of the ordinary.

31:35.961 --> 31:38.862
That was not an easy time
in my life.

31:38.864 --> 31:41.465
I was basically

31:41.467 --> 31:45.102
Sleeping with one foot
touching his every night,

31:45.104 --> 31:48.972
Sleeping with one eye open,
not getting any sleep at all,

31:48.974 --> 31:51.241
Constantly terrified.

31:51.243 --> 31:53.677
♪

31:53.679 --> 31:57.247
"is this the night
that my life ends?"

31:57.249 --> 32:03.654
♪

32:03.656 --> 32:09.960
♪

32:09.962 --> 32:13.697
I wanted to have enough evidence

32:13.699 --> 32:15.966
That somebody
would pay attention.

32:15.968 --> 32:19.303
♪

32:19.305 --> 32:21.538
I was watching a tv show.

32:21.540 --> 32:25.409
It was a crime show
about this woman

32:25.411 --> 32:28.378
That was recording her
conversations with her mother

32:28.380 --> 32:32.082
To try to get her mother to
confess to killing her father.

32:32.084 --> 32:35.319
And just, like,
this light bulb went on,

32:35.321 --> 32:38.155
And I said, "I'm going
to start recording

32:38.157 --> 32:41.291
My conversations with karl."

32:41.293 --> 32:43.560
I decided to move out.

32:43.562 --> 32:47.097
I fed him the story that we need
a trial separation.

32:47.099 --> 32:48.632
We'd been fighting about money,

32:48.634 --> 32:51.702
And, "let's just separate
for a while."

32:51.704 --> 32:55.172
And then, you know,
I started texting karl

32:55.174 --> 32:58.442
And saying to him
that I'm considering

32:58.444 --> 33:00.143
Getting back together with him,

33:00.145 --> 33:02.412
But that, "I can't get back
together with you

33:02.414 --> 33:04.047
Unless you're going
to be truthful

33:04.049 --> 33:06.416
About everything that happened
in our marriage.

33:06.418 --> 33:09.019
So, if you're interested,

33:09.021 --> 33:11.688
Let's set up a meeting time,
and we'll meet."

33:11.690 --> 33:14.891
And he jumped right on it.

33:14.893 --> 33:18.195
And here I am
with this voice recorder,

33:18.197 --> 33:19.997
And I'm going to go and try

33:19.999 --> 33:22.632
To get him to confess to murder.

33:22.634 --> 33:32.442
♪

33:32.444 --> 33:34.845
Oh, my god.
He's going to try to kill me.

33:43.889 --> 33:50.227
♪

33:50.229 --> 33:53.663
Best: Here I am
with this voice recorder,

33:53.665 --> 33:55.532
And I'm going to go and try

33:55.534 --> 33:58.168
To get him to confess to murder.

33:58.170 --> 34:00.070
-Hey.
-Hey.

34:00.072 --> 34:03.273
♪

34:03.275 --> 34:04.708
I was very nervous,

34:04.710 --> 34:08.779
And I was afraid
that he would catch on.

34:08.781 --> 34:12.349
So, my goal in the beginning
of recording karl

34:12.351 --> 34:14.051
Was if I could just get him

34:14.053 --> 34:16.853
To maybe confess
to setting the barn fire,

34:16.855 --> 34:19.990
It would at least
show his character.

34:19.992 --> 34:22.692
Thanks for meeting
with me.

34:22.694 --> 34:24.995
I know we haven't really
worked everything out.

34:24.997 --> 34:28.865
I guess I just don't know
what you want to discuss.

34:28.867 --> 34:32.903
Of course,
he completely denied it.

34:32.905 --> 34:35.772
I was trying to keep my cool,
and I said to him,

34:35.774 --> 34:37.641
"I can't get back together
with you

34:37.643 --> 34:39.943
Unless you're going
to be truthful."

34:39.945 --> 34:41.745
He said, "it sounds like
you want me to say

34:41.747 --> 34:46.483
I had something to do
with levi's death."

34:46.485 --> 34:48.685
And it was at that moment
that I thought,

34:48.687 --> 34:50.587
"okay, we're not going
to go to the barn fire.

34:50.589 --> 34:53.256
We're going
right to levi's death."

34:53.258 --> 34:57.527
♪

34:57.529 --> 34:59.796
So, I just said to him,

34:59.798 --> 35:02.265
"I would think
that if you<i> did</i> do it,

35:02.267 --> 35:06.036
You probably did it for me,
because of all the turmoil

35:06.038 --> 35:10.974
That levi put us through
as a teenager."

35:10.976 --> 35:15.278
Once I suggested that, he said,
"yes, I did it for you."

35:15.280 --> 35:18.715
I just wanted to stop
all the anguish.

35:18.717 --> 35:22.252
I thought it might help us.

35:22.254 --> 35:25.655
I'm thinking, "oh, my gosh.
I have it on tape."

35:25.657 --> 35:28.425
I said, "tell me
how it went that day.

35:28.427 --> 35:30.961
Was the truck hard to push?"

35:30.963 --> 35:32.863
And he said,
"no, it wasn't hard."

35:32.865 --> 35:36.166
And he gave me an example
of, like, a wheelbarrow,

35:36.168 --> 35:39.269
How a wobbly wheelbarrow
would be.

35:39.271 --> 35:42.839
I barely even touched the truck,
and it just...

35:42.841 --> 35:44.407
Fell.

35:44.409 --> 35:48.011
♪

35:48.013 --> 35:49.312
It was so surreal to me

35:49.314 --> 35:52.749
That I was getting him
to talk about this, but also

35:52.751 --> 35:56.786
Just hearing it come out
of his mouth horrified me...

35:56.788 --> 35:58.755
♪

35:58.757 --> 36:01.725
...Thinking what levi
must have gone through

36:01.727 --> 36:03.660
During those moments.

36:03.662 --> 36:06.796
I couldn't wait to finish
the conversation

36:06.798 --> 36:12.969
And just run it
to the sheriff's office.

36:12.971 --> 36:14.804
I gave him an excuse

36:14.806 --> 36:17.974
That I needed to drive
over to my doctor's office

36:17.976 --> 36:20.911
To pick up a prescription,

36:20.913 --> 36:22.779
Made sure he wasn't
following me,

36:22.781 --> 36:24.147
Then I drove around

36:24.149 --> 36:26.917
And went back
to the sheriff's office.

36:26.919 --> 36:34.824
♪

36:34.826 --> 36:36.359
They did not hear
the confession.

36:36.361 --> 36:39.362
It was too noisy,
too much background noise.

36:39.364 --> 36:41.831
They could hear my questions
and my answers to him,

36:41.833 --> 36:43.900
But they could not hear
what he was saying.

36:43.902 --> 36:45.702
And I was horrified.

36:45.704 --> 36:47.671
♪

36:47.673 --> 36:52.342
The sheriff's office asked me
if I would meet with karl again,

36:52.344 --> 36:55.712
Only this time
wearing their wire.

36:55.714 --> 36:58.715
And, of course, I said yes.

36:58.717 --> 37:02.085
♪

37:02.087 --> 37:04.754
I set up a meeting
with karl again,

37:04.756 --> 37:06.923
Encouraged him that I'm happy

37:06.925 --> 37:09.159
That things are moving
the way that they're moving,

37:09.161 --> 37:11.461
But we still had
more talking to do,

37:11.463 --> 37:14.664
And, "can we meet again
for lunch?"

37:14.666 --> 37:18.835
And so, when I arrived,
karl was waiting for me.

37:18.837 --> 37:23.773
♪

37:23.775 --> 37:25.709
He seemed suspicious.

37:25.711 --> 37:31.248
♪

37:31.250 --> 37:35.185
I'm scared half to death,

37:35.187 --> 37:36.353
But I'm trying not to be.

37:36.355 --> 37:39.489
I'm trying to keep it cool
and collected.

37:39.491 --> 37:43.693
♪

37:43.695 --> 37:45.128
I started right in with,

37:45.130 --> 37:48.231
"okay, things still
aren't making sense to me

37:48.233 --> 37:49.933
About what happened."

37:49.935 --> 37:56.706
♪

37:56.708 --> 37:59.309
Unfortunately,
he changed his story.

37:59.311 --> 38:01.478
He didn't tell me the same thing

38:01.480 --> 38:03.680
That he had told me
two days before.

38:03.682 --> 38:05.682
And, you know,
I argued with him.

38:05.684 --> 38:12.989
♪

38:12.991 --> 38:20.363
♪

38:20.365 --> 38:23.500
So, it's at this point,

38:23.502 --> 38:25.435
When I'm recording him,

38:25.437 --> 38:29.306
I'm realizing
that he's changed his story,

38:29.308 --> 38:32.876
And he's going to try
to convince me

38:32.878 --> 38:36.813
That what I had heard
two days before

38:36.815 --> 38:38.315
Wasn't real.

38:38.317 --> 38:47.824
♪

38:47.826 --> 38:57.400
♪

38:57.402 --> 39:07.043
♪

39:09.014 --> 39:13.183
So, karl is actually admitting
that, now at this point,

39:13.185 --> 39:16.619
That he accidentally
knocked the truck over on him

39:16.621 --> 39:18.154
And walked away.

39:18.156 --> 39:24.861
♪

39:24.863 --> 39:26.963
I was hopeful that maybe
that was something

39:26.965 --> 39:28.965
That they could use.

39:28.967 --> 39:31.134
I wasn't sure,
but I was hopeful.

39:31.136 --> 39:39.142
♪

39:39.144 --> 39:47.117
♪

39:47.119 --> 39:55.091
♪

39:55.093 --> 39:56.893
I've never seen that clip.

39:56.895 --> 39:59.462
I can tell
that karl's still trying

39:59.464 --> 40:02.031
To maintain control

40:02.033 --> 40:05.468
Of the situation.

40:05.470 --> 40:08.505
I think karl, at this point,
is a little bit desperate

40:08.507 --> 40:12.842
And not sure how
it's going to go for him.

40:12.844 --> 40:19.382
♪

40:19.384 --> 40:25.922
♪

40:25.924 --> 40:27.524
When I got the call,

40:27.526 --> 40:32.128
Just relief beyond belief.

40:32.130 --> 40:35.298
This huge weight lifted
off my shoulders.

40:35.300 --> 40:37.934
♪

40:37.936 --> 40:40.036
Alex was safe, I'm safe,

40:40.038 --> 40:43.072
And...

40:43.074 --> 40:45.575
Everything was going to be okay.

40:45.577 --> 40:48.545
But because he made
a plea deal,

40:48.547 --> 40:51.381
His plea was 15 years to life.

40:51.383 --> 40:54.951
Technically, in 2027,

40:54.953 --> 40:57.287
He's eligible for parole.

40:57.289 --> 41:05.995
♪

41:05.997 --> 41:14.637
♪

41:14.639 --> 41:18.074
For two years, I went through
this chronic pelvic pain

41:18.076 --> 41:20.677
That started out subtle
in the beginning

41:20.679 --> 41:24.781
But just kept getting worse
and more painful.

41:24.783 --> 41:27.917
You know, I went to the doctor,
and they did testing

41:27.919 --> 41:30.987
And kind of unexplained,
not sure why.

41:30.989 --> 41:34.491
It was when it went away
that I started thinking,

41:34.493 --> 41:37.594
"why did it go away
when I left karl?"

41:37.596 --> 41:39.963
♪

41:39.965 --> 41:42.198
I was talking to the p.I.,

41:42.200 --> 41:45.201
And he said to me, "cindy,

41:45.203 --> 41:49.138
Do you know that
one of the signs and symptoms

41:49.140 --> 41:52.809
Of arsenic poisoning
is pelvic pain?"

41:52.811 --> 41:55.812
It's something that I'll
probably always wonder --

41:55.814 --> 42:00.750
Wonder about if he was
actually poisoning me.

42:00.752 --> 42:02.485
I couldn't help but think

42:02.487 --> 42:06.689
How did his derangement

42:06.691 --> 42:08.758
Not show through before?

42:08.760 --> 42:16.366
♪

42:16.368 --> 42:19.702
He doesn't look deranged
in this picture at all.

42:19.704 --> 42:23.006
He doesn't look like
a scary monster

42:23.008 --> 42:27.143
Or anything like that,
like you would see on tv.

42:27.145 --> 42:32.215
This is the karl karlsen
that everybody knew...

42:32.217 --> 42:34.083
And I loved at one point.

42:34.085 --> 42:36.619
I loved him.

42:36.621 --> 42:40.723
It's such a hard thing
to come to grips with.

42:40.725 --> 42:43.660
Who was I married to?

42:43.662 --> 42:46.729
Why didn't I see this before?

42:46.731 --> 42:49.032
Why?
